# Project Standards

## Code Quality

- Do not write spaghetti code. Keep functions and components focused on a single responsibility.
- Avoid repetition. Extract shared logic into reusable helpers in `lib/` and shared UI into `components/ui/`.
- Prefer Server Components; use `'use client'` only when interactivity requires it.
- All Supabase queries belong in `lib/` — never duplicate data access in page components.

## Commit & Push Discipline

- Commit like a senior developer: small, focused commits with clear intent.
- Review changes before committing — no debug code, unused imports, or unrelated files.
- All commit messages must be written in **English**.
- Use conventional commit prefixes when appropriate: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`.
- Do not include agent names, tool names, or "Co-authored-by" lines in commits or push messages.

## Architecture

- Match existing naming, types, and file structure conventions.
- Keep diffs minimal — solve the problem without over-engineering.
